The paper discusses the training and comparison of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image recognition tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of CNNs also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the learning of parameters over time, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents a visual analytics approach, which could be considered a sub-topic of scientific visualization (cs.SI).
